# English Only

All text content in the codebase must be written in English.

## Rules

1. **Comments**: All code comments must be in English
2. **Documentation**: All documentation (README, MDX, JSDoc) must be in English
3. **Commit Messages**: Git commit messages must be in English, following Conventional Commits format
4. **Code Strings**: Avoid Chinese characters in string literals (enforced by ESLint)

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ Good
// Handle button click event
const handleClick = () => { ... };

// ❌ Bad
// 处理按钮点击事件
const handleClick = () => { ... };
```

## Commit Message Format

```
feat(Button): add loading state support
fix(Modal): correct z-index stacking issue
docs(README): update installation instructions
```

## Commit Message Restrictions

Do NOT include AI-generated co-author signatures in commit messages:

```
# ❌ Bad - Remove these lines from commits
Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Co-authored-by: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>

# ✅ Good - Clean commit message
feat(Button): add variant support for icon buttons
```
